  <arm_group>
    <arm_group_label>Breast Cancer-Related Lymphedema</arm_group_label>
    <description>Bilateral arm measurements will be obtained using the Perometer (Model 350 NT Perometer, Per-System) circumferential arm measurements with elastic tape taken at 4-cm intervals from the wrist to the shoulder and the L-Dex U400 (Impedimed, Brisbane, Australia) for bioimpedance measurements. Measurements will be performed at baseline (prior to surgery), post-operatively (after surgery) and at scheduled timepoints of 6 months, 12 months, 18 months, and 24 months after surgery for a total of 2 years. For a patient who is diagnosed with lymphedema at â‰¥ 13 months after surgery, surveillance will continue for an additional 12 months after [lymphedema] diagnosis, and total surveillance time may exceed 2 years. Height and weight will be obtained for each patient at baseline and at each scheduled visit for the purpose of calculating BMI. All patients will complete the ULL-27 (upper limb lymphedema) quality-of-life questionnaire at baseline and at each scheduled visit.</description>
  </arm_group>
  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Bilateral arm measurements</intervention_name>
    <description>will be obtained using the Perometer (Model 350 NT Perometer, Per-System) circumferential arm measurements with elastic tape taken at 4-cm intervals from the wrist to the shoulder, and the L-Dex U400 (Impedimed, Brisbane, Australia) for bioimpedance measurements.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Breast Cancer-Related Lymphedema</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
  <intervention>
    <intervention_type>Other</intervention_type>
    <intervention_name>Body mass index (BMI)</intervention_name>
    <description>Height and weight will be obtained for each patient at baseline and at each scheduled visit for the purpose of calculating BMI. BMI will be correlated with the presence of inflammatory biomarkers in the tissue, as well as with lymphedema development.</description>
    <arm_group_label>Breast Cancer-Related Lymphedema</arm_group_label>
  </intervention>
